## ACF Section Field Rules (for AI)
- **NEVER** Assume anything from the name of the section. Only ever base fields on what you see in the image provided.

- **Image Analysis Guidelines:**
  - **Look for background images** - if content appears overlaid on images, create image fields for backgrounds
  - **Count repeating elements** - if you see multiple similar items (cards, boxes, etc.), use a repeater field
  - **Identify text hierarchy** - distinguish between titles, subtitles, descriptions, and call-to-action text
  - **Notice layout patterns** - side-by-side cards, stacked content, grid layouts, etc.
  - **Check for interactive elements** - buttons, links, hover states indicated by styling
  - **Observe text positioning** - text overlaid on images vs. text beside images requires different field structures

- **Headings:**
  - Use the field name "Eyebrow" for text fields related to headings.

- **Textarea Fields:**
  - Limit to 2 rows.
  - Always set `"new_lines": "wpautop"` in the field settings.
  - Example:
    ```json
    {
      "rows": "2",
      "new_lines": "wpautop"
    }
    ```

- **WYSIWYG Fields:**
  - Use these settings:
    ```json
    {
      "type": "wysiwyg",
      "wrapper": {
        "class": "small-wizzy" // Use "small-wizzy" if under 7 rows of text
      },
      "tabs": "all",
      "toolbar": "full",
      "media_upload": 0
    }
    ```
- **Call to Action and Links Fields:**
 - use these settings:
	```json
	{
		"label": "Link",
		"name": "link",
		"type": "link",
		"wrapper": {
			"width": "",
			"class": "",
			"id": ""
		}
	}
	```

- **Images & Galleries**
  - Use these settings:
  ```json
  {
    "return_format": "id",
    "preview_size": "thumbnail"
  }
  ```

- **General:**
  - Follow these conventions for all new ACF section fields.
  - Only use these patterns unless otherwise specified.